subSubSection.paragraph:
Last visible abdominal sternite (
VII
) with one pair of marginal setae in male and with two pairs in female, in both sexes rounded at apex (in male more widely).

Median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs. 3 & 4
) in dorsal view wide, almost parallel-sided, in lateral view arcuate, with middle portion of ventral margin almost straight and with apical portion rather sharply bent dorsally, its ventral side edged laterally in apical part and slightly depressed between margins; terminal lamella in dorsal view large, about as long as wide or slightly wider than long, deeply concave, with sides roundly converging to rounded apex. Apical orifice in dorsal position, wide apically. Internal sac with large folded formation in middle portion of median lobe and without spines.

Female genitalia (
Figs. 5 & 6
): gonocoxite narrow and comparatively long, about 0.7 times as long as gonosubcoxite, with relatively narrow base.
